olive oil
1 packet spaghetti
1 clove garlic
1 packet diced bacon
1 sachet Herb & Mushroom Seasoning
½ packet cream
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Rocket leaves
drizzle balsamic vinegar
pinch chilli flakes
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet chicken breast

• Half-fill a large saucepan with water, add a generous pinch of salt, then bring to the boil over high heat.
• Cook spaghetti in boiling water until ‘al dente’, 9 minutes.
• Reserve pasta water (1/4 cup for 2 people / 1/2 cup for 4 people). Drain spaghetti, then return to saucepan.

• Meanwhile, cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook chicken and diced bacon, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 6-7 minutes.
• Add herb & mushroom seasoning and garlic paste and cook, until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Reduce heat to medium, add cream (see ingredients) and the reserved pasta water, and simmer, until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, add the cooked spaghetti and add half the baby spinach leaves and toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine the remaining spinach, rocket leaves and balsamic glaze.
• Divide creamy bacon, chicken and spinach spaghetti between bowls.
• Serve with spinach & rocket salad. Garnish spaghetti with a pinch of chilli flakes (if using) and grated Parmesan cheese. Enjoy!